2:13 PM Defendant Alexander J Booth in court.  Attorney Nicholas Martinez in court for Alexander J Booth. District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Nikole Kane. 

State files amended information. 

Defendant enters a no-contest plea to amended count #1 and amended count #2. Court conducts plea colloquy and finds the Defendant guilty of count #1 and count #2 of the amended information. 

Victim makes statements. State gives sentencing recommendations. Defense makes sentencing recommendations. Defendant makes statements. 

Court orders the following:

COUNT #1
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
60 Days Jail, STRAIGHT TIME

Term of Probation: 18 MONTHS
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
No VIOLENT contact with: victim listed in criminal complaint;

COSTS:  $243.00
DV Surcharge: $100.00
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
To be paid as a Condition of Probation.

CONDITION TIME: 30 days, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  

COUNT #2
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
60 Days in the Waukesha County Jail w/Huber (all standard release conditions) (2 days credit), CONSECUTIVE TO IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE IN COUNT #1, IF IMPOSED

Term of Probation: 18 MONTHS, CONCURRENT TO COUNT #1

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
SAME AS COUNT #1;

COSTS:  $243.00
DV Surcharge: $100.00
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
To be paid as a Condition of Probation.

Appeal rights given. 

Upon Petition - Court will consider early termination of probation at any point after 12 months, if all conditions are met and agent deems appropriate.

09:44 AM Defendant Alexander J Booth in court with attorney Nicholas Martinez.  Randy P. Sitzberger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Waive reading of Information.  NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED.  Atty. Martinez requests a date 60 days out for defendant to complete counseling.  Hearing scheduled for June 2, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Preliminary hearing on March 30, 2022 at 09:15 am.

CONDITIONS MODIFIED ON 03/10/2022:  Defendant to have NO VIOLENT contact with Victim A listed in the Criminal Complaint/Victim Identification Key.  Defendant is not to share, reproduce or distribute any personal and/or identifying information about the crime victim(s), except to their attorney.  If DNA sample has not been taken from the defendant, the Court orders sample to be taken;  and it may be expunged under 165.77(4) Wis. Statutes.  Absolute sobriety, defendant is not to possess or consume any alcohol.  Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.  Defendant not to possess any drug paraphernalia.  Defendant to report/comply with Wisconsin Community Services Pretrial Supervision Program under Level 2 supervision.  CAM duration pursuant to Pretrial Supervision Program protocols.  Defendant to pay costs associated with CAM.  Defendant to report to WCS within one business day.

10:32 AM Defendant Alexander J Booth in court.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Charlie Hoffmann appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court notes there is a letter on file from Victim A requesting for a no violent contact order.  The Court further notes Attorney Martinez previously filed a formal motion to modify bail conditions and an adjournment request that was denied.  The State has no objection to a no violent contact order.  Victim A appears in Court and requesting to have contact with the defendant.  The Court granted the Motion to Modify Bail.  The Court will schedule the preliminary hearing within 20 days and if that date does not work with Attorney Martinez he can file a letter with the Court requesting a new date.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for March 30, 2022 at 09:15 am.
Bail/bond hearing on March 17, 2022 at 10:00 am.
Notice of Motion and Motion To Modify Conditions of Bond (Modify the No Contact with Victim A to No Violent Contact).

Requesting to reschedule the hearing currently set for March 10, 2022 @ 10 am.

03/09/22 - Court Reviewed - Per Judge Schimel - Pursuant to the requirements of Marsy's law the court will not adjourn the hearing and unfortunately the court cannot adequately say victim notification can be provided for such a short turnaround. The court will allow Mr. Martinez's motion to be scheduled for a later date, but the status date remains. ep
03/09/22 - Clerk notified Attorney Martinez of the response by phone - voice message left. ep
